{"type":"message","id":"060b29cc","parentId":"c6b32588","timestamp":"2026-03-31T01:58:37.504Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[Mon 2026-03-30 21:58 EDT] [Subagent Context] You are running as a subagent (depth 1/1). Results auto-announce to your requester; do not busy-poll for status.\n\n[Subagent Task]: Transcribe 20 YouTube videos from Alex Finn's OpenClaw content. Save each transcript as a separate file.\n\n**FOLDER:** ~/Desktop/new alex finn transcripts/\n\n**VIDEOS TO TRANSCRIBE (in order):**\n\n1. https://youtu.be/UlC7pTdH_y4\n2. https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=qRA0MyPlEPE\n3. https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=CxErCGVo-oo\n4. https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Rjd1LqF9cG4\n5. https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=RhLpV6QDBFE\n6. https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=vxpuLIA17q4\n7. https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=XeTgMEapbag\n8. https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Aj6hoC9JaLI\n9. https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=HjQ5ty3_X_0\n10. https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=_kZCoW-Qxnc\n11. https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=41_TNGDDnfQ\n12. https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ev4iiGXlnh0\n13. https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=2KWhHY0KTMk\n14. https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=iGkhfUvRV6o\n15. https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=tqhmgHfT7v4\n16. https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=lxfakTpdz1Y\n17. https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=UTCi_q6iuCM\n18. https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=b-l9sGh1-UY\n19. https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=04wh2Hlgbds\n20. https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Qkqe-uRhQJE\n\n**FOR EACH VIDEO:**\n1. Use summarize tool: `summarize \"URL\" --youtube auto --extract-only`\n2. Get the video TITLE from the URL (strip off any &t= parameters)\n3. Create a file named: VIDEO_TITLE.txt (clean up special characters in filename)\n4. Start each file with:\n   ---\n   Video URL: [direct link]\n   ---\n\n**TIPS:**\n- Strip &t= parameters from URLs for filenames\n- If a title has special characters (/, ?, &, etc), replace with underscores or remove them\n- Include the FULL transcript (use --extract-only flag)\n- Work efficiently - transcribe multiple videos in parallel if possible\n- Save progress - don't lose work if it takes a while\n\n**OUTPUT:** 20 separate .txt files in the folder, one per video."}],"timestamp":1774922317501}}
{"type":"message","id":"105c716f","parentId":"060b29cc","timestamp":"2026-03-31T01:58:41.865Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I need to transcribe 20 YouTube videos from Alex Finn's OpenClaw content. Let me start by reading the summarize skill to understand how to use it properly, then work through the videos.\n\nFirst, let me read the summarize skill.","thinkingSignature":"dbfbf6806fc573a8229d40d28e21f82cd45f3f140b2c4c6db4f58c5bf0738155"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_7zgos2iqgozp_1","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"/opt/homebrew/lib/node_modules/openclaw/skills/summarize/SKILL.md"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":45,"output":94,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":17179,"totalTokens":17318,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774922317503,"responseId":"061a5d4d38a89a6799ad5e77a241b77f"}}
{"type":"message","id":"07fc6126","parentId":"105c716f","timestamp":"2026-03-31T01:58:41.888Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_7zgos2iqgozp_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\nname: summarize\ndescription: Summarize or extract text/transcripts from URLs, podcasts, and local files (great fallback for “transcribe this YouTube/video”).\nhomepage: https://summarize.sh\nmetadata:\n  {\n    \"openclaw\":\n      {\n        \"emoji\": \"🧾\",\n        \"requires\": { \"bins\": [\"summarize\"] },\n        \"install\":\n          [\n            {\n              \"id\": \"brew\",\n              \"kind\": \"brew\",\n              \"formula\": \"steipete/tap/summarize\",\n              \"bins\": [\"summarize\"],\n              \"label\": \"Install summarize (brew)\",\n            },\n          ],\n      },\n  }\n---\n\n# Summarize\n\nFast CLI to summarize URLs, local files, and YouTube links.\n\n## When to use (trigger phrases)\n\nUse this skill immediately when the user asks any of:\n\n- “use summarize.sh”\n- “what’s this link/video about?”\n- “summarize this URL/article”\n- “transcribe this YouTube/video” (best-effort transcript extraction; no `yt-dlp` needed)\n\n## Quick start\n\n```bash\nsummarize \"https://example.com\" --model google/gemini-3-flash-preview\nsummarize \"/path/to/file.pdf\" --model google/gemini-3-flash-preview\nsummarize \"https://youtu.be/dQw4w9WgXcQ\" --youtube auto\n```\n\n## YouTube: summary vs transcript\n\nBest-effort transcript (URLs only):\n\n```bash\nsummarize \"https://youtu.be/dQw4w9WgXcQ\" --youtube auto --extract-only\n```\n\nIf the user asked for a transcript but it’s huge, return a tight summary first, then ask which section/time range to expand.\n\n## Model + keys\n\nSet the API key for your chosen provider:\n\n- OpenAI: `OPENAI_API_KEY`\n- Anthropic: `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY`\n- xAI: `XAI_API_KEY`\n- Google: `GEMINI_API_KEY` (aliases: `GOOGLE_GENERATIVE_AI_API_KEY`, `GOOGLE_API_KEY`)\n\nDefault model is `google/gemini-3-flash-preview` if none is set.\n\n## Useful flags\n\n- `--length short|medium|long|xl|xxl|<chars>`\n- `--max-output-tokens <count>`\n- `--extract-only` (URLs only)\n- `--json` (machine readable)\n- `--firecrawl auto|off|always` (fallback extraction)\n- `--youtube auto` (Apify fallback if `APIFY_API_TOKEN` set)\n\n## Config\n\nOptional config file: `~/.summarize/config.json`\n\n```json\n{ \"model\": \"openai/gpt-5.2\" }\n```\n\nOptional services:\n\n- `FIRECRAWL_API_KEY` for blocked sites\n- `APIFY_API_TOKEN` for YouTube fallback\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774922321881}}
{"type":"message","id":"833a262e","parentId":"07fc6126","timestamp":"2026-03-31T01:58:46.111Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good, now I understand how to use the summarize tool. I need to use `summarize \"URL\" --youtube auto --extract-only` to get the full transcript. Let me start processing the videos. I'll run multiple in parallel to be efficient.\n\nFirst, let me create the output directory and then start transcribing the videos. I'll process them in batches since there are 20 videos.","thinkingSignature":"d2638ab3a7d0f3465ed621ec95d1f2a0ab3c5860a741daa9c34e42dec753f15f"},{"type":"text","text":"Let me create the output directory and start transcribing the videos in parallel batches.\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_hb5key427551_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"mkdir -p ~/Desktop/new\\ alex\\ finn\\ transcripts"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":1386,"output":133,"cacheRead":16546,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":18065,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774922321889,"responseId":"061a5d51cf6251a151f2e37a20e42e5a"}}
