al for\nyour working life that you don't have to\nmanage or track yourself. It's all done\nautomatically. So, I'm going to show you\nhow it works, then I'll give you the\nprompt for it so you can build it\nyourself. My OpenClaw built this\ndashboard out for me for all our daily\nmemories. By default, OpenClaw doesn't\ntrack daily memories. Now with this, it\ndoes. And now I can go back and any day\nin any month in any year, I can see what\nme and my Open Claw discussed on that\nday. So if I built an app a couple\nmonths ago and I forgot how it worked or\nI forgot how I built it, I can go all\nthe way back to a specific day that I\nbuilt it, click on that day, and now I\ncan see the exact things I built and did\non that day. I can see on this random\nday I clicked on January 27th, I built\nout the brains and the tools model where\nwe implemented different models for\ndifferent use cases inside openclaw\nwhich saved a ton of money. And now I\ncan see exactly how we built that out\nand what we discussed to build that out.\nAnd even the more impactful part about\nthis is this now drives the entire\nmemory system for my open claw. Ever\nsince I implemented this daily memory\nsystem, my open claw has never forgot a\nthing. It remembers everything. I can\nsay hey remember that project we started\nthree months ago let's resume it and\nthen now my open clock can start working\non it again it did not do that before so\nyou need to implement this daily memory\nsystem it it allows you to track\neverything you do in intense detail and\nimproves the memory your open claw by\n10x so here's how you set it up let's go\ninto telegram and I'll give you the\nprompt down below as well that you can\njust copy and paste I want to set up a\ndaily memory system we should have logs\nfor every day we work together every\ndiscussion we have. You should put a\nsummary into this daily tracker system.\nThen you should refer back to this\nlogging system whenever I have questions\nabout specific projects or days. Please\nbuild out this dashboard. If you have a\nmission control like I do, like you can\nsee right here, you can just say, \"Hey,\nadd it to our mission control for me.\"\nIf you don't know what mission control\nis or you want to know how to build it,\nI'll put a link down below for a video\nin which I explain how to build out the\nmission control. It's basically a hub\nfor all these custom tools we can build\nout. I think this is the first thing you\nshould set up with your open claw so you\ncan improve its memory and you can start\ntracking all your work. I can't wait\ntill like 5 years from now and I can\nlook back and I can see everything I was\nworking on from 5 years ago day in and\nday out. I think that's going to be\nreally cool to have. So memory tracking\nsystem improves your open claw and\nallows you to track all your work.\nThat's a great use case. But this next\nuse case helps me make sure I'm on top\nof all the news the moment it breaks and\nit keeps my content trending so I can\nkeep getting more and more eyes. And\nthis is my trending content alert. In\nDiscord, I have this channel alerts. And\nin this channel, Henry will alert me the\nmoment any sort of content starts\ntrending that talks about things I'm\ninterested in. So, if there's a tweet\nabout Claude Code or if there's a Reddit\npost about Open Claw that goes super\nviral, I will get alerted the moment\nthat happens so that I can a know about\nthings people care about and stay on top\nof the latest breaking news, but b stay\non top of trends. If you're a content\ncreator, the most important thing you\ncan do to go viral is talk about\ncuttingedge trending topics. This allows\nyou to do that. So, this not only helps\nme stay on top of what people are\ntalking about, what's important, but\nalso keep my content trending so I can\nkeep growing my audience. So, right now,\nfor instance, the top trending post on\nXabout Claude Code, someone just posted\nthis getting 2,000 likes, is about vibe\ncoding inside VR headsets. So, now I\nknow people care about vibe coding in VR\nheadsets. Now, I can go and create a\nYouTube video that shows people how to\nvibe code in VR headsets. This is how\nyou stay on top of trends, find the\nlatest and greatest tools the moment\npeople start talking about them, and\nkeep your content relevant to your\naudience. You got to implement this. And\nthe way you implement this is very, very\nsimple. So, here's the prompt you need\nto steal. I'll put it down below. Use\nthe X API, Reddit API, and YouTube API\nto track trending content in Claude\nCode, Open Claw, and AI. Those are the\nthree subjects I care about. You can put\nin whatever subjects you want. every\nhour, spin up a sub agent that checks\nthese platforms for what's trending in\nthose topics. Then send me the best\ntrending content to an alerts Discord\nchannel. If you haven't set up your\nDiscord yet, it is a great platform to\nset up these kind of advanced workflows\nin OpenClaw. I also put a link down\nbelow for the setup of Discord and\nOpenClaw. But you hit send on this. What\nyou're going to need to set up is the X\nAPI, Reddit API, YouTube APIs. Your\nOpenClaw will walk you through that.\nThey'll ask you for API keys. They'll\ntell you how to get the API keys. Reddit\nand YouTube are free. The XAPI costs per\ncall, so it's up to you. I think it's\nworth it. It's not too expensive, but if\nyou want to stick with free, you can\njust do Reddit and YouTube. But you get\nthat set up and you're now going to get\nthe latest breaking news the moment it\nstarts trending on social media. You'll\nbe up to date on everything you care\nabout, and you can make amazing content.\nThat use case is amazing because it\nkeeps you on top of news. But this next\nuse case is great because it's going to\nhelp you save money on software and\nbuild out any tool you need the moment\nyou need it. And that use case is vibe\ncoding. Vibe coding inside of OpenClaw\nis so awesome. I