 development team and they\nhave helped my business so much. It's\nhelped totally change the direction of\nthe different apps I'm building. No\nmatter what it is you do, whether you\nhave a 9 to5, a career, a family,\nwhatever it is, you should set up your\nown research and development team that\nwill help come up with ideas and guide\nyou on whatever it is you care about. If\nyou have a career, they can review what\nyou're doing in your career and give you\nadvice for getting promotions and\nraises. If you're getting started in\ncontent, it can review your tweets and\ngive you recommendations for what you\ncan put out. If you have a family that\ncan come up with new ideas for things\nyou can do together, for planning\nvacations, whatever it is, you need an\nautonomous research and development team\nworking for you all the time. And it's\nreally cheap, too. We've had four memos,\nand each one's cost me 10 cents. So, I'm\ngetting really good results from this\nfor really cheap. So, here's the prompt\nyou want to use. I'll put this down\nbelow. I want a research and development\nteam that works for me 247. It should be\na team of five different AI models that\nlook at what I'm working on, come up\nwith new ideas, then debate those ideas\namongst themselves. They then build me a\nfinal memo that gives me new\nrecommendations for things I can do to\nimprove my apps or generate more\nrevenue. Please set up a dashboard for\nthis. I'll put this down below as well\nso you can just copy it. It's going to\nchoose five different AI models for you.\nYou're going to have to set up APIs with\neach. It'll walk you through that. Super\nsimple and easy to do. You don't need to\nbe technical for it. My team goes twice\na day. So 9:00 a.m. 5:00 p p.m. They\nhave the debates amongst themselves and\ngive me the report. You can have it do\nonce a day if you want, five times a day\nif you want. Whatever your budget is,\nyou can build a team around that. But\nthis is one of the most powerful use\ncases of AI is having intelligence that\ncan come up with new ideas for you, that\nsees things in different perspectives,\nand that can help autonomously advance\nyour business. No matter what it is\nyou're doing in your career, you need a\nresearch and development team that can\nwork for you. Steal this prompt and get\nthis done. That is a great use case. But\nthis next use case is probably my most\nrequested use case to explain. And that\nis the overnight employee. Every single\nnight, my open claw goes and builds\nsomething it thinks that can push my\nbusiness forward for me. It does it\nproactively and it does it autonomously.\nI don't ask for these specific things.\nOne of my favorite things it's built for\nme is this feedback dashboard. This is a\ndashboard that plugs into my SAS creator\nbuddy and actually collects feedback\nfrom users for me. We were having\ndiscussions where I had no feedback\nmechanism in my SAS. So, one night it\nproactively and autonomously went and\nbuilt out this feedback widget for me\nthat that plugged into my SAS and now I\ncan get feedback that people leave me on\nmy app creator buddy. Then I can go and\nfix bugs or implement features that were\nrequested from me. This proactive\novernight employee is one of the best\nreasons to be on OpenClaw. This is\nsomething Chad GPT can't do. This is\nsomething Claude Code can't do. This is\nsomething only OpenClaw can do. But how\ndo you set this up? How do you have your\nopen claw proactively and autonomously\njust do things for you? Just build\nthings for you? You got to prompt it the\nright way. Here's the prompt you need to\nsteal. I'll put this down below for you.\nI want you to be a proactive and\nautonomous employee. Every night at 2\na.m. That's the key part here. Please\ntake a look at my business, what we've\ndone together, and our goals and\nobjectives. Then do one task you believe\nwill bring us closer to those goals and\nobjectives. Every task should bring us\none step closer to our goals. I need you\nto be an autonomous employee. So,\nthere's a couple key things going on\nhere. The biggest thing is this. Every\nnight at 2 am, what that is doing is\nactually scheduling a cron job for your\nopen claw. Cron jobs are just scheduled\ntasks. What that cron job will do is\ntrigger at 2 am every morning and cause\nyour open claw to go reflect on your\nbusinesses, what you've done together,\nyour missions, your objectives, your\ngoals, and figure out one task it can do\nto bring you closer to those goals.\nEvery morning I wake up and I wake up to\na surprise, something my open claw did\novernight to get us closer to those\nobjectives. This is how you build that.\nSometimes it'll build you a micro app.\nSometimes it'll write you a plan, a\nscript, a tweet if that's something\nyou're interested in. It'll just do\nsomething to get you closer to your\ngoals. This is how you set it up to be\nautonomous. If you do these five things\nI just showed you in this video right\nnow, you steal the prompts down below.\nYour open claw is going to be humming.\nYou're going to get so much productivity\nout of it and you'll have no idea how\nyou're doing life without openclaw\nbefore. This upcoming Friday, I'm going\nto do a live boot camp in the vibe\ncoding academy that will go over all my\nuse cases and everything I do in\nOpenClaw. So, if you're interested in\nthat, link for the Vibe Coding Academy\nis down below. If you learned anything\nhere at all, please leave a like down\nbelow and let me know in the replies\nwhat you want me to talk about next in\nmy next video. Everything I do here is\nbased on your feedback and replies from\nall my videos. So, let me know. I'm\nthinking about doing my long awaited\nlocal models video on how to use Open\nClaw with local models. That might come\nnext. So, let me know. Make sure to\nsubscribe and turn on notifications. All\nI do is make amazing videos about AI.\nand I will see you in the next\n\n3.0s · 14m 32s YouTu