sessed. It's\nbeen the most amazing tool I've ever\nused. Can't wait to see you again. I'll\nbe talking to you soon. See you in the\nnext video.\n\n2.6s · 13m 46s YouTube · 3.1k words · text via transcript/captionTracks","cwd":"/Users/bobbygalletta/.openclaw/workspace-yoyos"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774922356132}}
{"type":"message","id":"8411d8bc","parentId":"8aa2ebc0","timestamp":"2026-03-31T01:59:16.135Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_1guixqntxoep_3","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Transcript:\nOpenClaw is the most powerful AI tool\never created, but only if you do these\nfive things right after you set it up.\nIf you don't do these five things I'm\nabout to show you, your OpenClaw is\nbasically just a glorified chat GPT. The\ngood news is, even if you're already set\nup, if you do these five things now, I\npromise your OpenClaw will be way more\nproductive. By the end of this video,\nyour OpenClaw will be a super\nintelligent 24/7 autonomous AI employee\nworking directly for you. Let's get into\nit. So, you just set up your Open Claw.\nIt's up and running. Maybe it's on a Mac\nMini. Maybe it's on an old dusty laptop.\nDoesn't matter. You want to do these\nfive things. The first of which is brain\ndump. You want to give your open claw\ncrucial context that will make it so\nmuch more powerful and personalized. But\nwhat should you brain dump to your open\nclaw? What should you tell it about you?\nThe good news is I got a perfect list\nready to go. So, here is what you want\nto tell your open claw immediately. And\nthe reason why this is so powerful is\nthe moment your open claw knows what\nyour interests are, your goals are, your\nambitions, what you're trying to achieve\nin life, it can start doing tasks\nautonomously for you that brings you\ncloser to those goals and ambitions. If\nit doesn't know what you're trying to\nachieve, how is it supposed to bring you\ncloser to your goals? How's it supposed\nto make your life more productive? The\nfirst thing you need to do is go in,\nbrain dump your interest. So, what you\nlike, what you're interested in. This is\ngoing to help it give you news you're\ninterested in. This is going to help\nkeep you up to date on niches you have\ninterest about. You want to give it all\nyour interests. These next three are\nprobably the most important. Your\ncareer, your goals, your ambitions. For\nme, OpenClaw has been instrumental on\nhelping me with my ambitions, on growing\nmy SAS creator buddy, on growing my\ndifferent content channels. I've gone\nfrom 50K subscribers to 120K subscribers\non YouTube since I started using\nOpenClaw. It has been incredible for me\nto get closer to all my goals. So, you\nwant to go in and you want to tell what\nyou're trying to achieve. Are you trying\nto get promoted at work? Are you trying\nto grow your social media? Are you just\ntrying to make more revenue overall? Are\nyou trying to learn something about AI?\nYou put that in and once it knows your\nambitions, it can start doing things for\nyou while you sleep to help you achieve\nthose goals and ambitions. So these are\nhyper hyper critical. And the good thing\nis is if you can't think of these, if\nyou're struggling to think of these, you\ncan do what's called reverse prompting.\nSo you can go to your AI, your Claw\nBond, and say, \"Hey, I'm trying to\nfigure out what my goals and ambitions\nare. Can you ask me a few questions that\ncan help pull it out of me?\" And your\nopen call will actually help tease those\ngoals and ambitions out of you. So if\nyou can't answer any of these five\nthings and put it into your open claw,\njust reverse prompt and your open claw\nwill help you figure what those are.\nGiving your open claw this context off\nthe rip will make it 10 times more\npowerful and help come up with tasks\nthat will be so much more productive for\nyou. The next thing you want to do with\nyour open claw is connect it to all of\nthe tools that matter to you. Open claw\nis great because it can pull data from a\n100 different sources so that it can do\ntasks more effectively. So for instance,\nI use things three as my personal\norganization tool. Every day I go in, I\nhave my tasks I need to complete and I\nfigure out what I have to do that day.\nOpenClaw can figure out how to connect\nto a lot of these tools and pull the\ndata in. So for instance, right after I\ngot started with OpenClaw, I said I use\nThings 3 for productivity. Can you grab\nmy tasks from that? It went online, it\nresearched the things 3 API and it was\nable to actually start pulling my tasks\ninto OpenClaw. Now every morning it\nautomatically looks at what I have to do\nthat day and starts taking tasks off my\nplate for me. Now I have an automated\nsystem where my AI is looking at all my\ntasks that day and just doing anything\nit can do for me and helping me out. I'm\ngetting so much more work done since it\nstarted connecting to my things three.\nSo whatever productivity tools you're\nusing, whatever communication tools\nyou're using, just brain dump into your\nopen claw all those tools and like okay\nI can connect to this. I don't know how\nto connect to this but let me figure\nthat out and it will connect to those\nthings. That's the best part about all\nthis is it's self-improving and the\nthings it doesn't know how to do, it\nwill just figure it out. So, put your\ntools in, lean on your OpenClaw, and it\nwill figure out how to connect to all\nyour tools for you and it will start\nincluding it in all its automated\nworkflows like it includes my to-do\nlist. Once your Open Claw knows\neverything about you, once it's starting\nto pull in data from all your other\ntools, it is time to create some custom\ntools for yourself. And the way I like\nto do that is with a mission control,\nwhich is what you see here. Now, I've\ntalked about mission control on a lot of\nmy videos. If you've watched them so\nfar, by the way, if you haven't watched\nthem so far, make sure to subscribe and\nturn notifications down below. I've\nliterally spent hundreds of hours in\nOpenClaw. So, I am going to pump out so\nmuch helpful content that will make you\na master. But the mission control is so\ncritical for your workflow, and it's so\ncritical you get it set up right away.\nWhat you're able to do in a mission\ncontrol is have your open claw build out\nany tools it needs as you're working\nwith it. So for instance, it was\nstarting to schedule a lot of its own\ntasks and I wanted to track all the\ntasks it was doing autonomously. So I\nsaid, \"Hey, can you build a calendar for\nus inside our mission control?\" And it\nwent and just built out this entire\ncalendar. I didn't have to code\nanything. It was writing a lot of\nplanning documents for me, but I didn't\nhave any way to see them. So I said,\n\"Hey, can you build a tool where I can\nreview all the documents you're creating\nfor me?\" And it went and built this\nentire docs tool. What you want to do\noff the rip is you want to set up a\nmission control. go to your OpenClaw,\nsay, \"Hey, I want a place, a mission\ncontrol where we can build out custom\ntools. Please build this in next.js and\nhost it locally.\" It will then build out\nthe shell of your mission control. And\nthen as you go, you can add your own\ncustom tooling in. If you want a couple\nof tools off the bat that you can make\nthat will be very helpful. You can make\na task tool that tracks all your tasks\nas your OpenClaw does them. You can\ncreate the calendar tool, which shows\nyou all the tasks your OpenClaw is doing\nautonomously. And then I would also set\nup the documents view so you can view\nall the documents it's creating. From\nthere you can just create custom tools\nas you go. If you're a content creator,\ncreate a content creation tool. Whatever\nyou need, you just build it as you go.\nAnd all you have to do is just tell your\nOpenClaw to build it for you. You don't\nneed technical knowledge to do this.\nThis mission control is where you're\ngoing to spend most of your time. So you\nwant it set up right away so you can\nstart pumping out those custom tools. By\nthe way, if you've learned anything so\nfar, make sure to leave a like down\nbelow. Also, this Friday, I'm doing a\nlive boot camp inside the Vibe Coding\nAcademy. I do it every single Friday,\nand if you join now, you get all of the\npast recordings, so you can watch them\nall. Make sure to join the community of\nover 700 people in the Vibe Coding\nAcademy. Link for that down below. I\npromise you'll have a fun time with me\nin there. Next, you want to figure out\nyour mission statement. This might be\nthe most important tip I give out of all\nfive of these. And that is creating a\nmission statement that both you and your\nopen claw can stick to. This is a\nmission statement that will be\nremembered with every single prompt you\ngive to your open claw. So that every\ntask it does, it brings you closer to\nthis mission statement. So for instance,\nfor me, my mission statement with my\nopen claw is an autonomous organization\nof AI agents that does work for me and\nproduces value 247. That's what I'm\ntrying to create. I'm trying to create a\ndigital company filled with agents just\ndoing work autonomously at all times.\nAnd so when I give my open claw task, I\nwanted to remember that mission\nstatement so that everything it does\nbrings us closer to that mission. You\nneed your own mission statement. This\nwill help make every task your open claw\ndoes that much more productive. So if\nI'm you, you have two options. You can\neither think of your mission statement\nif you know one and then go in and say,\n\"Hey, create a mission statement and put\nat the top of our mission control so you\nremember it with everything we do or if\nyou don't know what your mission\nstatement should be.\" Again, a perfect\nopportunity to reverse prompt. Say,\n\"Hey, OpenClaw, based on everything you\nknow about me, based on our tasks and\nour workflows, what should our mission\nstatement be? What should the one\nstatement be that you remember with\nevery single task that will help us be\nmore productive and bring us closer to\nthe goals and ambitions we talked about?\nYou create that mission statement. You\nsay, \"Put it at the top of your mission\ncontrol.\" And now moving forward,\neverything it does, every decision it\nmakes, every task it does will have that\nmission statement in mind so you get\ncloser to your goals. This is like a way\nof taking your massive giant laser that\nis open claw and having it focused on\none point. That's what the mission\nstatement is. You need to create that\nmission statement to be more productive.\nSo, those have been four things you need\nto do right when you get set up. Here's\nthe fifth thing. The fifth thing you\nneed to do right when you get set up is\nset expectation with your open claw\naround how you want to work together\nwith it. The number one complaint I get,\nI think, is, \"Oh, my open claw isn't\nproactive at all. You keep talking about\nhow your OpenClaw does tasks for you\nautonomously and proactively. Mine\ndoesn't do that. How the hell are you\ndoing that? I did it because I set\nexpectations with my open claw. That's\nhow I wanted it to work. So, what does\nthat mean? How do you set expectations\nwith your open claw? When you get hired\nat a company, you typically sit down\nwith your boss and your boss goes, I'd\nlike you to come in at these times. I'd\nlike you to do this. I'd like you to\ntake care of this and I'd like you to\nhandle this. That sets the expectation\nof what you want to do. But so many\npeople don't do that with their open\nclaw. need to treat it like an employee\nand talk to it the same way. So, when I\nstart with my open call, I literally\nwent in and I'll put this prompt down\nbelow so you can steal it. I say this,\nyou are my autonomous, proactive\nemployee. I want you to do work with me\nthat brings us closer to our mission\nstatement. I want to wake up every\nmorning and be pleasantly surprised by\nthe work you completed. Please schedule\ntime for every night and afternoon to do\na task that brings us closer to our\nmission statement. What this will do is\ncause your AI employee, your open claw\nto understand what your working\nrelationship will be and also it will\nstart scheduling regular task every\nsingle night to get you closer to your\nmission statement. This is how your open\nclaw becomes proactive. And that's why I\nsaid at the beginning of this video, if\nyou don't do these things, you're just\nusing basically a glorified chat GPT\nbecause it doesn't just do things for\nyou. You need to set those expectations.\nSo take this prompt, put it in, and your\nopen claw will start being a lot more\nproactive for you, and you'll wake up\nevery morning like, \"Oh, wow. It did\nthis for me. This is incredible.\" You do\nthese five things, your open claw is\ngoing to be so much more productive. I\npromise you. Let me know down below if\nany of these five things you haven't\ndone yet, and which ones you're planning\nto do immediately. Also, if you've done\nanything to make your open claw more\nproactive, let me know down below, too.\nI'll include it in my next video. Again,\nif this was helpful, leave a like. Make\nsure to subscribe and turn on\nnotifications and check out the Vibe\nCoding Academy down below. So glad you\nwatch my videos.\n\n2.6s · 10m 40s YouTube · 2.4k words · text via transcript/captionTracks"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":3090,"aggregated":"Transcript:\nOpenClaw is the most powerful AI tool\never created, but only if you do these\nfive things right after you set it up.\nIf you don't do these five things I'm\nabout to show you, your OpenClaw is\nbasically just a glorified chat GPT. The\ngood news is, even if you're already set\nup, if you do these five things now, I\npromise your OpenClaw will be way more\nproductive. By the end of this video,\nyour OpenClaw will be a super\nintelligent 24/7 autonomous AI employee\nworking directly for you. Let's get into\nit. So, you just set up your Open Claw.\nIt's up and running. Maybe it's on a Mac\nMini. Maybe it's on an old dusty laptop.\nDoesn't matter. You want to do these\nfive things. 