{"type":"message","id":"515614d8","parentId":"cddf0a1b","timestamp":"2026-03-31T01:59:31.286Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_e5uqy0fcoo8c_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Transcript:\nThis is the video you've been waiting\nfor. The number one question I've gotten\nover the last few weeks since OpenClaw\nreleased is, \"Okay, I get the technology\nis powerful, but how does this actually\nmake my life better?\" In this video, I'm\ngoing to answer that question. I'm going\nto go through six lifechanging open claw\nuse cases that I personally guarantee\nwill be applicable to everyone watching\nthis video. I don't care if you've never\ntouched a computer in your life or\nyou're a complete technical wizard,\nyou're going to find at least one\nworkflow in this video that will\nconvince you that Open Claw is the most\npowerful technology of all time. Now,\nlet's lock in and get into it. The first\nuse case I want to go through is a\nsecond brain. Have you ever been on the\nroad and you came up with an idea or\nfound a link you wanted to remember or a\nbook you wanted to read, but you didn't\nhave a system for saving any of that?\nand maybe you're using something like\nnotion or Apple notes. But the issue is\nboth those tools can get very complex,\nespecially when you start putting a lot\nof information into it. I built a second\nbrain system with Open Claw that helps\nme remember everything I think of all\nwith just a simple text message.\nOpenclaw has the best memory system of\nany AI tool ever created. It remembers\nliterally everything you tell it. So,\nyou need to take advantage of this\nmemory system. So, I built this second\nbrain system you see here, which allows\nme to view and search through every\nconversation we've ever had. This is\namazing because now at any time, I can\ngo into Telegram or iMessage or Discord\nor wherever I'm communicating with my\nbot and just send it things to remember.\nSo, maybe you're on the road and your\nfriend tells you about a book you want\nto read. What you were probably doing\nbefore is maybe you'd go into notion,\nyou go into this really complex folder\nsystem, or maybe go into Apple Notes,\nwhich has 10,000 notes in it that you'll\nnever read ever again. With OpenClaw, I\ncan simply just text message anything to\nmy bot Henry, say, \"Hey, please remember\nthis for me,\" and then come back into my\nsecond brain system at any point and\nfind those memories very easily. So, for\ninstance, if I'm on the road and I find\na book about local LLM, I can say,\n\"Remind me to read a book about local\nLLMs.\" I can hit enter. That text Henry\nto remember whatever that is I was\ntalking about. And what's amazing is you\ncan do this literally from iMessage and\nsend that there. And then in my second\nbrain system that I built here that I'll\nshow you how to build yourself in a\nsecond with OpenClaw. I can now go in\nand either search through my memories.\nIf I hit command K, I have this global\nsearch. And now I can say local LLMs.\nAnd now I have every single memory and\ndocument and task I've ever given Henry\nand can find it very very easily and pop\nit open and read it here. This is the\nmost powerful second brain system in the\nworld. One, because it remembers\nliterally everything. And two, I don't\nneed to use annoying complex apps like\nnotion. I can just text my Open Claw\nfrom my phone and it remembers\neverything I text it. That's again the\nmost amazing part about Open Claws. The\ninterface is so simple. You don't need\napps. You don't need anything that you\njust text message your bot. Now, you\nwant to build this yourself. Very\nsimple. I got good news for you. Your\nopen claw is super intelligent. It can\ndo anything you ask it. I'll put this\nprompt down below, so feel free to copy\nand paste it into your own open claw.\nBut what you want to say is, I want to\nbuild a second brain system where I can\nreview all our notes, conversations, and\nmemories. Please build that out with\nNex.js. You hit enter on that, and your\nopen claw will literally just build out\nthis entire system for you. It does the\nvibe coding for you. You're not even\nvibe coding anymore. Your bots's doing\nthe vibe coding. I didn't touch a line\nof code to build what you saw here. I\njust told my OpenClaw to build it, and\nit went and built it for me. Everyone\nneeds a second brain system. So, if you\nhaven't yet, go to your OpenClaw, text\nit, say, \"Hey, build this for me.\" You\ncan text it from the road and it'll\nbuild it on your computer, and you will\nhave your second brain system all set up\nand good to go. The second use case that\nI'll go through that I promise will make\nyour life so much easier is the custom\nmorning brief. Every morning at 8:00\na.m., my bot Henry sends me a completely\ncustom morning brief with everything I\nneed to know going into that day. This\nis scheduled. I don't need to think\nabout it, and includes all the important\ninformation I need to know. So, for\ninstance, it tells me the biggest AI\nstories from the last night, so that\nwhen I wake up, I instantly know\neverything I need to know from the news.\nIt gives me a bunch of video ideas. So,\nyou can see here, I have three ideas for\nnew videos I can film. And what you\ndon't see here is it actually wrote the\nentire scripts for these videos, too.\nSo, I can just wake up and I have\nscripts ready for me, good to go. It\ntakes a look at my to-do list on my Mac\nand tells me any tasks I need to\ncomplete that morning. And then it\nrecommends me tasks it can do itself to\nhelp me out. This ensures the moment I\nwake up, I have all the information I\nneed. And also, I already have work\ndone. I'm literally up for one minute\nand I already have multiple scripts\nwritten out, good to go. I've used\nseveral of these scripts over the last\ncouple weeks, and I bet you didn't even\nrealize it was built by my bot, Henry.\nThis morning brief alone has saved me\nseveral hours a week. And the best part\nis is you can customize this any way you\nwant with one simple message. And the\nreason you can do this and the reason\nwhy this is so powerful is is a few\nthings. Open Claw has complete access to\nthe internet. So while I'm sleeping, it\nliterally opens up a browser, just sits\nthere and researches on the internet all\nnight long. And then two, it does task\nproactively. So it will schedule this\nand send me these morning briefs at the\nsame time every morning. And even\nbetter, on top of all that, it goes\ndirectly to my phone. So this is all\ntexted to me through Telegram. So I\ndon't need to go in these confusing\nthird party apps to find these morning\nbriefs. They're all texted directly to\nme in the apps I use daily and I get all\nthe information I need and tasks done\nthe moment I wake up. So, how do you set\nthis up yourself? Very simple. Go to\nyour open claw and type this in. I want\nto set up a regular morning brief. Every\nmorning, I want you to send me a report\nthrough Telegram. I want this report to\ninclude one new stories relevant to my\ninterest, two ideas for businesses I can\ncreate, three tasks I need to complete\ntoday, and four recommendations for\ntasks we can complete together today.\nAnd you can customize this any way you\nwant. Literally anything you want in\nyour morning brief, you just put it into\nthis message. The reason why I really\nlike number four is it actually has the\nAI come up with its own tasks that it\ncan help you with. So, it thinks of\nthings on its own that you maybe you\ndidn't know it could do, but you hit\nenter on this and it will go and it just\nwill schedule and do this for you. No\ntechnical work needed. And after just 5\nseconds, you now have a morning brief\ncoming in every morning with all the\nimportant information you need to know\nand a brief on what you need to do that\nday. It doesn't matter what industry\nyou're in or what you do. You can create\na custom morning brief that will be\nhelpful for your life and save you time.\nAnd if you can't think of what you want\nin that morning brief, I have even\nbetter news for you. You don't even have\nto think of things to put in your brief.\nYou can just say, \"I want this report to\ninclude things relevant to me.\" You can\njust say, \"Hey, think of things to put\nin this report.\" So, you don't even need\nto creatively think about it. You can\njust lean on your open claw to think of\nwhat to put in that report. Easy peasy\nprompt down below. Steal it. Put it in.\nYou instantly have more value in your\nlife. The third thing I built with my\nopen claw that has changed my life that\nI think will change a lot of other\npeople's lives is really relevant if\nyou're into content creation. Whether\nyou tweet or you create YouTube videos\nor you write newsletters or you do\nliterally anything to do with content, I\nthink this one's relevant to you. And if\nyou have absolutely no interest in\ncontent, you don't write any content,\nfeel free to skip to the next chapter.\nBut I built my own content factory. I\nuse Discord for this because Discord is\ngreat for channels. So, I'd highly\nrecommend going in and setting up your\nOpenClaw in Discord if you don't know\nhow to literally just go to your Open\nClaw and say, \"Hey, set up a Discord for\nus.\" And what I have my Open Claw do is\na few things every morning. One, it\nresearches the top content opportunities\nthat day. So, it'll go research the top\nstories. It'll research content trending\nfrom my competitors. It'll research\nthings performing well on social media.\nAnd then, it'll come up with those ideas\nfor content. Then Henry takes this\nresearch and passes it off to another\nagent, Quill, who then takes this and\nactually writes scripts. So it takes one\nof the ideas that Quill thinks is the\nbest, and then writes an entire script\nfor that idea. And this doesn't have to\njust be scripts, it could be tweets if\nyou want, it 