 get very complex,\nespecially when you start putting a lot\nof information into it. I built a second\nbrain system with Open Claw that helps\nme remember everything I think of all\nwith just a simple text message.\nOpenclaw has the best memory system of\nany AI tool ever created. It remembers\nliterally everything you tell it. So,\nyou need to take advantage of this\nmemory system. So, I built this second\nbrain system you see here, which allows\nme to view and search through every\nconversation we've ever had. This is\namazing because now at any time, I can\ngo into Telegram or iMessage or Discord\nor wherever I'm communicating with my\nbot and just send it things to remember.\nSo, maybe you're on the road and your\nfriend tells you about a book you want\nto read. What you were probably doing\nbefore is maybe you'd go into notion,\nyou go into this really complex folder\nsystem, or maybe go into Apple Notes,\nwhich has 10,000 notes in it that you'll\nnever read ever again. With OpenClaw, I\ncan simply just text message anything to\nmy bot Henry, say, \"Hey, please remember\nthis for me,\" and then come back into my\nsecond brain system at any point and\nfind those memories very easily. So, for\ninstance, if I'm on the road and I find\na book about local LLM, I can say,\n\"Remind me to read a book about local\nLLMs.\" I can hit enter. That text Henry\nto remember whatever that is I was\ntalking about. And what's amazing is you\ncan do this literally from iMessage and\nsend that there. And then in my second\nbrain system that I built here that I'll\nshow you how to build yourself in a\nsecond with OpenClaw. I can now go in\nand either search through my memories.\nIf I hit command K, I have this global\nsearch. And now I can say local LLMs.\nAnd now I have every single memory and\ndocument and task I've ever given Henry\nand can find it very very easily and pop\nit open and read it here. This is the\nmost powerful second brain system in the\nworld. One, because it re