to your Open\nClaw and say, \"Hey, set up a Discord for\nus.\" And what I have my Open Claw do is\na few things every morning. One, it\nresearches the top content opportunities\nthat day. So, it'll go research the top\nstories. It'll research content trending\nfrom my competitors. It'll research\nthings performing well on social media.\nAnd then, it'll come up with those ideas\nfor content. Then Henry takes this\nresearch and passes it off to another\nagent, Quill, who then takes this and\nactually writes scripts. So it takes one\nof the ideas that Quill thinks is the\nbest, and then writes an entire script\nfor that idea. And this doesn't have to\njust be scripts, it could be tweets if\nyou want, it could be newsletters if you\nwant, whatever you want. Then from\nthere, the scripts are passed off to\nanother sub agent, Pixel, who then goes\nand actually generates AI thumbnails for\nthe videos. So, what you can see here is\nactually a local AI model that's running\non my Mac Studio that generates images.\nYou can use Nano Banana for this. You\ndon't need to use a local model. I just\nlike to use a local model. I'm still\ntraining this local model now to make\ngood thumbnails, but very soon I will\nhave very good AI thumbnails printing\nout. The point being is you can set up\nthese complex systems inside Discords\nwhere you have multiple agents in\ndifferent channels basically running a\ncontent factory for you. Here's the\nprompt you're going to use to set it up.\nI put this down below as well. Feel free\nto put it into your Telegram or Discord\nor whatever communication your channel\nyou're using with your Open Claw. I want\nyou to build me a content factory inside\nof Discord. Set up channels for\ndifferent agents. Have an agent that\nresearches top trending stories, another\nagent that takes those stories and\nwrites scripts, then another agent that\ngenerates thumbnails. Have all their\nwork organized in different channels.\nYour OpenClaw will go and set this all\nup for you. You don't need technical\nknowledge. It will just set it up, set\nup the different agents, and have them\nworking. Then from there, you can ask it\nto do it regularly. I have this happen\nat 8 a.m. every morning. 8 a.m. every\nmorning, each agent does that work. So,\nthey'll do the research and then it'll\ngenerate scripts, then it'll generate\nthumbnails. You can customize this any\nway you want. If you're more focused on\nX, you can say, \"Generate me threads,\ngenerate me posts.\" If you're more\nfocused on newsletters, you can just\nsay, \"Hey, write me newsletters\ninstead.\" This is completely custom.\nThat's the beautiful part about all of\nthis. So, take that prompt, build your\nown content factory. The next use case I\nwant to go over is great for anyone who\neither a wants to build their own\nbusiness or b needs to do research for\ntheir own business. They already have.\nThere is this incredible skill from Matt\nVan Horde called the last 30 days skill.\nWhat this skill does is allow OpenClaw\nto research any topic you can think of\nand see what people are saying about it\non Reddit and X. So for instance, say\nyou're a wannabe entrepreneur. You want\nto start your own business. You want\nOpenClaw to build an app for you, but\nyou don't know what to build an app\nabout. You install this skill, which\nI'll show you how to do in a second.\nThen you go into your open claw and you\nsay something like, \"Please use the last\n30-day skill to research challenges\npeople are having with OpenClaw.\" And\nfor you, you can put in any topic or\nsubject you want in there. Then your\nOpenClaw will go in and actually\nresearch both X and Reddit over the last\n30 days and find all the challenges with\nOpenClaw, right? And so if I'm thinking\nabout this from an entrepreneurial\nperspective, I'm thinking, okay, what\nchallenges are people having here? Since\nI am a major voice in OpenClaw, I could\npotentially build a product that solves\none of these challenges. So, okay. So,\nlooks like people are having setup\ndifficulty now. Maybe I go and build a\nsystem where it makes it much easier to\nset up the open claw. Right? This is how\nentrepreneurs think. They look for\nchallenges and then build solutions to\nthose challenges. Now, taking this a\nstep further, I can go in and I can ask\nmy open claw, hey, build a product that\nsolves this challenge. And now my open\nclaw will go and vibe code a solution to\nany of these challenges. Then I ship it\nand I'm good to go. I got a product\ngoing. This is basically a software\nfactory that I built. I didn't have to\ncode. I didn't have to do any technical\nwork. I just set up these skills and now\nmy open claw is doing all this work for\nme. Anyone can do this. There's no\nspecial skill I have that allowed me to\ndo what I just showed you. You whether\nyou have a nineto-ive kids, I don't\ncare. You can install this skill and\nliterally within 15 seconds have a\nsystem set up where you are building\nproducts that you can sell and start\nmaking money off of. There is no\nhyperbole here. If you think I'm lying\nabout any part of this, tell me which\npart of this I'm talking about that\nisn't true. I will have the link to this\nlast 30 days skill down below. You\nsimply copy and paste it into your open\nclaw and say install this skill and\nboom, you have the skill and you're good\nto go. If you found any of this helpful\nso far, make sure to leave a like down\nbelow. Make sure to subscribe and turn\non notifications. All I do is create\nincredible videos about AI and OpenClaw.\nLet me know down below which of these\nuse cases have been the most helpful so\nfar. I still have two more to go before\nwe get to these last two. Just let me\nknow which have been the most helpful\nbefore. And if you have any questions\nfor me, feel free to join the Vibe\nCoding Academy. I'm doing a live boot\ncamp this Friday. It will be recorded.\nYou can be a part of it. You can ask me\nquestions, anything you want. It's all\npart of the open claw boot camp that\nwill be in the Vibe Coding Academy link\ndown below. Join us for that. The next\nuse case that I promise will help every\nsingle person watching this video, no\nmatter how skeptical you are about\nOpenClaw is giving OpenClaw tasks that\nmove you closer to your goals. Now, what\ndoes that mean? Open Claw can do\nanything a human being can do on a\ncomputer. The challenge most people have\nwith OpenClaw is you got all this power\nin the world, but they can't think of\nwhat to do with it. So, what I built\nhere that I'm about to show you is a\nsystem for OpenClaw to figure out tasks\nit can do on its own that gets you\ncloser to your goals. So, I built out\nright here this canban board. By the\nway, every time I say canban, I get a\n100 comments and say, \"Oh, you're\npronouncing it wrong.\" I don't care. I'm\ngoing to say canban. What happens is\nevery morning, Henry, my openclaw, puts\nin its own tasks and starts getting to\nwork on those tasks. These tasks always\nget me closer to what my overall goals\nare in my career. Right? So, right now\nit's researching ExoLabs, which is\ntechnology allows me to run local models\non my Mac Studio, but you can see a lot\nof the other tasks it's done over the\nlast day. It's edited my mission control\nhere. By the way, if you want\ninstructions on how to build your own\nmission control UI, let me know in the\ncomments down below as well. It's\nresearching ExoLabs. It's building a new\ncouncil functionality that allow me to\ntalk to a bunch of models at the same\ntime. And this is all doing things that\nhelp me get closer to my goals. But how\ndoes it know what my goals are and how\ndoes it figure out what it should do?\nWhat I'm about to show you is the most\nimportant workflow you can do in Open\nClaw today, which is this. Brain dump\ninto Open Claw every goal, mission,\nobjective you have in your life, your\npersonal life, and your career. This\ngives context to Open Claw around\neverything you're trying to accomplish.\nRight? So for me, I'm trying to grow my\nYouTube. I'm trying to grow my\neducational community. I'm trying to\nbuild incredible products. I'm trying to\nscale my SAS creator buddy. And I brain\ndumped all that into my OpenClaw. Now\nthat OpenClaw knows all my missions and\nobjectives in my life, I can give it a\nprompt that says, \"Hey, every morning at\n8:00 a.m., come up with four to five\ntasks that you can do on my computer\nthat brings me closer to these goals.\"\nNow, OpenClaw every morning goes in,\ncomes up with its own tasks, schedules\nthem for itself, and completes those\ntasks. doing research for me, building\nscripts for me, writing content for me,\nbuilding new functionality in my mission\ncontrol for me. All these little things\nget me closer to my end goals. You\nshould do this as well. So, two steps\nyou need to do right now. Go into\nTelegram or however you're communicating\nwith your open claw. Brain dump all your\ngoals and then say, \"Hey, every morning\ncome up with tasks you can complete that\nget me closer to these goals.\" And then\nif you want to take it a step further\nlike me, you can say, \"Hey, build out a\ncanban board that tracks these tasks so\nyou can see every single thing your bot\nis doing.\" This system will basically\nturn your bot into a close employee that\nworks for you that you can track. You\nneed to do this. The only people that\nshouldn't be doing what I just\nrecommended are people with no goals or\nambitions in your life. And if you have\nno goals and ambitions in your life, why\nthe hell are you watching this channel?\nGet the hell out of here. This channel's\nfor high ambition people only. And the\nlast use case I'll give you, the sixth\nout of six use case I'll give you is\nbuild your own mission control. What you\nsee here, why should you build your own\nmission control? My goal with my mission\ncontrol app here is I want to replace\nevery piece of software I use. Notion,\nto-d doist, it doesn't matter what app I\nuse. I want to replace it and build it\nmyself with my openclaw. And the reason\nwhy I want to do that is Open Claw has\naccess to every memory, everything\nyou've ever told it. By building out\nyour own apps, by building your own\ncalendar tools and note-taking tools and\nall of that, you now have tools that are\ndirectly integrated with every memory\nand conversation you've ever had with\nAI, which is incredibly powerful. And it\ndoesn't even account for the fact that\nnow I don't have to pay for these other\ntools. I'm just building them myself.\nSo, as long as you're using computers\nand you have apps on your computer, this\nuse case is impactful for you. You're\nbasically just having your OpenClaw\nbuild out all the apps you're already\nusing. And this isn't complicated. You\njust go to your OpenClaw and you say,\n\"Hey, I'm tired of using Google\nCalendar. Please build out our own\nversion using NextJS.\" And you hit enter\nand it'll just build you the app and\nit'll ship it and launch it and run it.\nand you just go to the URL it gives you\nand you have your own calendar app and\nyou don't need to use Google calendar\nanymore as long as you use software\nwhich I assume if you're watching this\nchannel and watching like a 20 minute\nlong openclaw video you probably have\napps you use this use case impacts you\nit saves you money and it supercharges\nyour apps because it plugs it into all\nyour openclaw memories right this is my\ncalendar this isn't just showing the\nevents on my calendar this is showing\nthe automated tasks my openclaw does\nevery day. So, that makes it a way more\npowerful calendar. Now, the last thing\nI'll go through on this video that I\nthink is really important is cost. The\n[laughter] I think the number one reply\nI get in all my videos is, \"Yeah, but\ntalk about cost. How much is this\ncosting you? Are you broke now?\" No,\nthis is only costing me $200 a month.\nThat's how much the anthropic\nsubscription costs. But you don't need\nto do this for $200 a month. You can do\nthis for way cheaper. Miniax just\nreleased a model called Miniax 2.5. It\nis incredibly powerful. It is basically\nas powerful as Opus and it is about $10\na month. You don't need to use Opus. You\ncan say, \"Hey, use Miniax instead and\nyou'll save money.\" There's a model\ncalled GLM5 that you can use. That's\nanother $5 a month. There are expensive\nways to do this like Opus and there are\ncheap ways to do this like Miniax. So\ndepending on what your budget is, you\nhave many different options. It's\ntotally up to you. I personally am going\nwith Anthropic because I think it's the\nbest coding model in the world, but you\ncan go with cheaper options. Let me know\ndown below which is going to be the\nfirst use case you implement. And also\nmore importantly, let me know down below\nwhat video do you want to see next about\nOpenClaw. Is there any specific use\ncase? Is there anything you want me to\nshow you how to set up? Let me know down\nbelow. I'm happy to go through. I'm\nthinking about doing a video around how\nto plug in local models to open claw so\nyou can save money with open models. Let\nme know down below if that's what you\nwant to see as well. I hope this is\nhelpful. Leave a like down below.\nSubscribe. Turn on notifications. Join\nthe vibe coding academy if you want to\nsee all the live boot camps I do. Hope\nthis was helpful and I'll see you in the\nnext\n\n0.0s · 18m 53s YouTube · 4.2k words · text via transcript/captionTracks","cwd":"/Users/bobbygalletta/.openclaw/workspace-yoyos"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774922371284}}
